t ein kulturgeschichtlicher Teil vorangestellt ist, der die Elite über die Historie und sozioökonomische Aspekte definiert.  aThe book tells the story of the Athenian elite between 600 and 400 BCE through the imagery on the luxury pottery from which the wealthy drank at their festivals. More than 6,000 analytic presentations lend insight into the lives of the elite as horse owners, athletes, and banquet socialites. The pictorial analysis is prefaced by a cultural historical section that describes the history and socio-economic situation of the elite.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aElite (Social sciences) in art. 0aElite (Social sciences)zGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLuxurieszGreecezAthens. 0aSocial status in art. 0aVase-painting, GreekzGreecezAthensxThemes, motives. 4aAntike Eliten. 4aLuxuskeramik. 4aklassisches Athen. 7aART / History / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient elites.  aclassical Athens.  aluxury pottery.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2017z9783110547733oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104533170 cprintz978311044973040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045411640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110454116423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110454116/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE